                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111660">Gazeley</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1381">1381</origDate>. 
                        Release from <persName nymRef="Brochslan"><forename>Christiana</forename>, widow of <persName><forename>William</forename> <surname>Brochslan</surname> of <placeName role="person">Clare</placeName></persName></persName> to <persName><forename>Robert</forename> of <surname>Kedytone</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>Richard</forename> <surname>Perfey</surname></persName>, and <persName><forename>Geoffrey</forename> <surname>Brochole</surname></persName>, of her right in the lands and tenements formerly in the possession of the said William, <persName><forename>John</forename> <surname>Talmage</surname></persName> and <persName><forename>Agnes</forename> <surname>Nichole</surname></persName>, in the vills and fields of <placeName>Nedham</placeName>, Gayslee, <placeName>Kenteforde</placeName>, <placeName>Kenyt</placeName>, and <placeName>Multone</placeName>. 
                        Dated at <placeName role="date">Clare</placeName> on Sunday [22 Dec.] after the feast of St Thomas Apostle, 5 Richard II [1381].
                        Endorsed. "Nicoles in Nedham."
                        The seal is wanting.
                     [Chandler deeds]
                     </p>
